description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Clinical Pharmacist Vacancies at Modality Repeat Prescribing Hub and/or Modality Walsall Practices&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary Range: WTE Circa from £38K dependent on qualifications and experience (pro-rata to hours worked)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent role in Walsall&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working 37.5 hours per week, between 8.30am and 6.30pm, Mon to Fri&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work as part of a multi-disciplinary team to develop and run processes for repeat prescription re-authorisation, management of medicines on transfer of care and systems for safer prescribing in addition to patient caseload management in acute and long-term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practice Specific Roles will include Medication Reviews, Medicine Management, Medicine Optimisation and working with the clinical team on long term conditions management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from pharmacists with a minimum of 2 years post-graduate experience. The successful candidates will have a degree in pharmacy and relevant professional registration. A post-graduate diploma or higher degree in clinical pharmacy is desirable. The ideal candidate will hold a prescribing qualification. An enhanced DBS check is required for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates with the appropriate level of experience and qualifications will be expected to mentor, support and develop pharmacy colleagues across the Walsall areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated individuals with good communication/customer service skills who is IT literate and who preferably have experience working in a similar environment/capacity previously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are Modality Partnership?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A growing super partnership providing primary care services to circa 450,000 patients across multiple GP Surgeries nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our focus is on delivering innovative, high quality patient-centred care whilst providing a supportive working environment for our multi-disciplinary teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Commitment to developing and sustaining a learning environment for exceptional health professionals of the future&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with local colleagues to deliver integrated care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proud of our professional friendly team who look after our patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provider of established and high quality services on site (outpatients, diagnostic, mental health, surgical)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team cover during absences, reducing backlog on your return&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A caring and supporting working environment for all our staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full introduction into Primary Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mentorship&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training and Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full induction programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Protected learning time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities to follow a career escalator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In-house practice meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Internal development appraisals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fairness, equality and honesty&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Practice social events&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we expect from our team;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To interact with patients to provide and process information in response to inquiries, concerns and requests about NHS services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dedicated, flexible individuals with high aspirations for themselves and for integrated primary care teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key skills in customer service orientation, communication, stress tolerance, listening and problem solving&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of relevant computer applications, Microsoft Word and EMIS Web [Desired but not essential as full training will be provided]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re currently looking for candidates to join the Modality team in the practices detailed above. If you’re positive about continuing to work as part of a fast-paced and continuously developing organisation then this could be the role for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Candidates will be contacted only if their application is taken further.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
